dings%20on%20a%20carrier%20than%20when%20trying%20to%20shake%20incoming%20surface-to-air%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22MQ-25%20Navy%20aircraft%20carrier%20USS%20George%20H.W.%20Bush%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F624683c17bf4e60019369d37%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221428%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20MQ-25%20on%20the%20flight%20deck%20of%20the%20aircraft%20carrier%20USS%20George%20H.W.%20Bush%20in%20December%202021.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%2FMCS3%20Brandon%20Roberson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20those%20difficulties%2C%20expanded%20use%20of%20drones%20is%20likely%20to%20have%20a%20number%20of%20benefits%20for%20navies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompared%20to%20carrier%20aircraft%20like%20the%20F%2FA-18%20or%20F-35%2C%20uncrewed%20aircraft%20tend%20to%20have%20lower%20operating%20costs%20and%20to%20require%20less%20equipment%20and%20fewer%20personnel%2C%20Hollings%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThat%20makes%20them%20a%20bit%20more%20flexible%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20repositioning%20them%20across%20ships%20or%20even%20theaters.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20usually%20have%20better%20endurance%20than%20crewed%20aircraft%2C%20even%20while%20piloted%20remotely%2C%20because%20crews%20can%20transition%20in%20and%20out.%20Getting%20rid%20of%20the%20crew%20onboard%20allows%20for%20lower%20overall%20weight%20or%20allocating%20more%20weight%20to%20fuel%2C%20cargo%2C%20or%20payload%2C%26quot%3B%20Hollings%20added.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20the%20biggest%20benefit%20is%20the%20reduced%20risk%20to%20human%20operators.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EConstantine%20Atlamazoglou%20works%20on%20transatlantic%20and%20European%20security.%20He%20holds%20a%20master's%20degree%20in%20security%20studies%20and%20European%20affairs%20from%20the%20Fletcher%20School%20of%20Law%20and%20Diplomacy.%20You%20can%20contact%20him%20on%20%3Ca%20data-xid%3D%5C%22fr1659647903195f