d%20its%20annual%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.defense.gov%2F2023%2FOct%2F19%2F2003323409%2F-1%2F-1%2F1%2F2023-MILITARY-AND-SECURITY-DEVELOPMENTS-INVOLVING-THE-PEOPLES-REPUBLIC-OF-CHINA.PDF%5C%22%3EChina%20Military%20Power%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20congressionally-mandated%20update%20of%20unclassified%20material%20and%20assessments%20on%20the%20People's%20Liberation%20Army.%20The%20latest%20report%20paints%20a%20picture%20of%20military%20developments%20in%202022%20and%20notes%20that%20the%20People's%20Republic%20of%20China%20(PRC)%20has%20been%20turning%20to%20the%20PLA%20%26quot%3Bas%20an%20increasingly%20capable%20instrument%20of%20statecraft%26quot%3B%20as%20it%20has%20become%20more%20coercive%20and%20aggressive%20in%20international%20affairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%2C%20the%20report%20says%2C%20has%20accelerated%20%26quot%3Bits%20development%20of%20capabilities%20and%20concepts%20to%20strengthen%20the%20PRC's%20ability%20to%20'fight%20and%20win%20wars'%20against%20a%20'strong%20enemy%2C'%26quot%3B%C2%A0a%20reference%20to%20Chinese%20leader%20Xi%20Jinping's%20expectations%20for%20the%20armed%20forces%20and%20rhetoric%20on%20China's%20primary%20rival%3A%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pentagon's%20report%20notes%20that%20China's%20fighter%20jet%20fleet%20has%20both%20expanded%20and%20apparently%20improved.%20By%20the%20end%20of%202022%2C%20the%20PLA%20Air%20Force%20(PLAAF)%20and%20PLA%20Navy%20(PLAN)%20had%201%2C300%20fourth-generation%20fighter%20jets%20out%20of%20its%201%2C900%20total%20fighters%20compared%20to%20800%20fourth-generation%20fighters%20out%20of%20its%201%2C800%20total%20at%20the%20end%20of%202021.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20implication%20is%20that%20not%20only%20did%20China's%20total%20fighter%20fleet%20expand%20by%20100%20aircraft%2C%20but%20it%20also%20seems%20to%20have%20replaced%20older%20aircraft%20with%20500%20more%20capable%20jets%20in%20the%20span%20of%20a%20year%2C%20a%20major%20jump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20PLAAF%20and%20PLAN%20Aviation%20continue%20to%20field%20greater%20numbers%20of%20fourth-generation%3Cbr%3Eaircraft%2C%26quot%3B%20DoD%20said%20in%20its%20report%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20Chinese%20military%20will%20%26quot%3Bprobably%20will%20become%20a%20majority%20fourth-generation%20force%20within%20the%20next%20several%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225187%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22New%20flight%20cadets%20line%20up%20to%20board%20the%20Y-20%20at%20an%20airport%20in%20Nanjing%2C%20Jiangsu%20province%2C%20China%2C%20July%2020%2C%202023.%20The%20Air%20Force%20uses%20the%20Y-20%20to%20welcome%20newly%20recruited%20Air%20cadets%20from%20six%20provinces%20and%20cities%20in%20Shanghai%2C%20Jiangsu%2C%20Zhejiang%2C%20Anhui%2C%20Jiangxi%20and%20Fujian%20to%20the%20Air%20Force%20Aviation%20University.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6536a35f96f7540cd0631bde%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223345%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENew%20flight%20cadets%20line%20up%20to%20board%20the%20Y-20%20at%20an%20airport%20in%20Nanjing%2C%20Jiangsu%20province%2C%20China%2C%20July%2020%2C%202023.%20The%20Air%20Force%20uses%20the%20Y-20%20to%20welcome%20newly%20recruited%20Air%20cadets%20from%20six%20provinces%20and%20cities%20in%20Shanghai%2C%20Jiangsu%2C%20Zhejiang%2C%20Anhui%2C%20Jiangxi%20and%20Fujian%20to%20the%20Air%20Force%20Aviation%20University.%3Cp%3ECFOTO%2FFuture%20Publishing%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EExamples%20of%20China's%20fourth-generation%20fighter%20aircraft%20include%20the%20Chengdu%20J-10%2C%20Shenyang%20J-16%2C%20and%20Shenyang%20J-15.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20J-10%20is%20a%20Chinese%20a%20single-engine%20multirole%20aircraft%20built%20for%20air%20combat%20but%20is%20capable%20of%20conducting%20other%20missions.%20It's%20development%20demonstrated%20China's%20ability%20to%20produce%20fourth-gen%20jets%2C%20and%20it%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fglobaltimesnews%2Fstatus%2F1638759563800489985%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edescribed%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Chinese%20media%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bbackbone%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20PLAAF.%20The%20newest%20variant%2C%20the%20J-10C%2C%20entered%20service%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20twin-engine%20J-16%20entered%20service%20around%202016%20and%20marked%20a%20notable%20capability%20jump%20in%20Chinese%20aviation%2C%20as%20the%20PLAAF%20began%20relying%20less%20on%20Russian%20technology%20and%20instead%20developing%20jets%20that%20matched%20or%20surpassed%20it.%20As%20a%20multirole%20strike%20fighter%2C%20the%20J-16%20are%20maneuverable%20and%20can%20carry%20more%20weapons%20than%20the%20fifth-gen%20J-20%2C%20including%20a%20variety%20of%20air-to-air%20missiles%2C%20anti-ship%20mis%20isles%2C%20and%20cruise%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20J-15%20is%20a%20heavy%20carrier-based%20fighter%20jet%20in%20service%20with%20the%20Chinese%20PLAN%2C%20which%20has%20three%20aircraft%20carriers%2C%20namely%20the%20Liaoning%2C%20Shenyang%2C%20and%20Fujian.%20While%20the%20J-15%20has%20undergone%20upgrades%20since%20it%20entered%20service%20in%202014%2C%20China%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20in%20the%20process%20of%20developing%20a%20more%20advanced%2C%20next-generation%20carrier-based%20fighter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20J-16%20multirole%20fighter%20jet%20takes%20part%20in%20a%20flying%20display%20at%20the%2014th%20China%20International%20Aviation%20and%20Aerospace%20Exhibition%20in%20Zhuhai%2C%20south%20China's%20Guangdong%20Province%2C%20on%20Nov.%208%2C%202022.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6536a9c496908fd7cdb54a7a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222031%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20J-16%20multirole%20fighter%20jet%20takes%20part%20in%20a%20flying%20display%20at%20the%2014th%20China%20International%20Aviation%20and%20Aerospace%20Exhibition%20in%20Zhuhai%2C%20south%20China's%20Guangdong%20Province%2C%20on%20Nov.%208%2C%202022%2C%3Cp%3ELiu%20Dawei%2FXinhua%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20China%20has%20been%20making%20other%20improvements.%20While%20China%20has%20%26quot%3Bhistorically%20struggled%20to%20field%20domestically%20built%20engines%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Pentagon%20report%20indicates%20they've%20made%20significant%20progress%20in%20development%20and%20production%2C%20Matthew%20P.%20Funaiole%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20with%20the%20China%20Power%20Project%20and%20senior%20fellow%20for%20data%20analysis%20with%20the%20iDeas%20Lab%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%20(CSIS)%20think%20tank%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20that%20includes%20switching%20out%20the%20Russian%20engines%20in%20its%20jets%2C%20such%20as%20the%20J-10%20and%20J-20%2C%20to%20domestically%20produced%20WS-10%20engines.%20According%20to%20the%20DoD%20report%2C%20although%20some%20Russian%20AL-31F%20engines%20likely%20remain%20in%20use%2C%20China%20has%20actively%20pushed%20to%20improve%20its%20domestic%20aircraft%20engine%20production%20and%20is%20now%20seeing%20better%20results%20as%20it%20upgrades%20its%20fighters.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%20developed%20in%20the%201990s%2C%20the%20WS-10%20turbofan%20engine%20has%20been%20tested%20in%20fighter%20jets%2C%20such%20as%20the%20J-11%2C%20for%20decades%2C%20but%20developers%20struggled%20with%20getting%20the%20engine%20to%20produce%20enough%20power%20for%20aircraft.%20The%20WS-10%20also%20needed%20constant%20refurbishing%20and%20care%20that%20proved%20to%20be%20more%20of%20a%20hassle%20than%20it%20was%20worth.%20Since%20being%20enhanced%20a%20number%20of%20the%20times%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20the%20WS-10%20is%20far%20more%20mature%2C%20giving%20China%20a%20domestically%20built%20engine%20it%20can%20install%20in%20aircraft.%C2%A0The%20J-10C%20was%20spotted%20with%20the%20engine%20during%20an%20exercise%20a%20couple%20years%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20is%20evident%20from%20the%20DoD%20report%2C%20the%20PLAAF%20is%20undergoing%20a%20comprehensive%20process%20of%20upgrading%20and%20expanding%20its%20assets%2C%20while%20also%20upskilling%20its%20personnel%2C%26quot%3B%20Funaiole%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20build-up%20of%20aerial%20assets%20is%20supported%20by%20China's%20domestic%20industrial%20base%20and%20its%20ongoing%20military-civil%20fusion%20efforts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-fighter-jet-fleet-growing-size-capability-pentagon-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698089467000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653698eb0487ff031cabc449%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-fighter-jet-fleet-growing-size-capability-pentagon-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Pentagon's%20new%20report%20on%20China's%20highlights%20its%20growing%20military%20might%2C%20including%20the%20addition%20of%20500%20fourth-gen%20jets%20to%20its%20fighter%20jet%20fleet.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cpanella%40insider.com%20(Chris%20Panella)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A27%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-fighter-jet-fleet-growing-size-capability-pentagon-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%225%20Big%20Changes%20As%20US%20Releases%20Proposed%20Tweaks%20To%20H-1B%20Process%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20H-1B%20visa%20program%20has%20long%20been%20a%20pivotal%20aspect%20of%20immigration%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20particularly%20for%20skilled%20professionals%20and%20international%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20recently%20unveiled%20a%20set%20of%20changes%20to%20the%20H-1B%20program%2C%20aimed%20at%20improving%20its%20integrity%20and%20flexibility%20while%20addressing%20the%20evolving%20needs%20of%20the%20American%20workforce.%20US-based%20author%20Soundarya%20Balasubramani%20decodes%20the%20proposed%20changes%20in%20the%20H-1B%20visa%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20More%20Multiple%20Entries%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20One%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20changes%20involves%20the%20elimination%20of%20multiple%20entries%20by%20employers%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20same%20employee.%20In%202023%2C%20over%20half%20of%20the%20approximately%20800%2C000%20H-1B%20registrations%20were%20multiple%20entries%2C%20artificially%20inflating%20the%20chances%20of%20some%20applicants.%20To%20combat%20this%2C%20an%20employee%20can%20only%20be%20registered%20once%2C%20and%20employers%20will%20now%20be%20required%20to%20submit%20passport%20information%20for%20each%20employee.%20This%20allows%20the%20United%20States%20Citizenship%20and%20Immigration%20Services%20(USCIS)%20to%20ensure%20a%20fair%20and%20equitable%20selection%20process.%20Attempts%20to%20bypass%20this%20rule%20will%20lead%20to%20denials%20or%20revocations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20Need%20For%20%26quot%3BEmployer-Employee%26quot%3B%20Relationship%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20The%20previous%20requirement%20for%20an%20%26quot%3Bemployer-employee%26quot%3B%20relationship%2C%20imposed%20in%202010%2C%20has%20been%20a%20significant%20hurdle%20for%20founders%20looking%20to%20secure%20H-1B%20visas%20through%20their%20own%20companies.%20The%20new%20rule%20eliminates%20this%20requirement%2C%20making%20it%20easier%20for%20entrepreneurs%20to%20utilize%20the%20H-1B%20program%20to%20build%20and%20grow%20their%20businesses%2C%20even%20if%20they%20own%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJob%20Offer%20Can%20Be%20Remote%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20In%20a%20nod%20to%20the%20post-pandemic%20world%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20(DHS)%20acknowledges%20that%20a%20bona%20fide%20job%20offer%20can%20now%20include%20telework%2C%20remote%20work%2C%20or%20other%20off-site%20work%20within%20the%20United%20States.%20This%20change%20aligns%20with%20the%20widespread%20adoption%20of%20remote%20work%20arrangements.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAutomatic%20%26quot%3BCap-Gap%26quot%3B%20Extension%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20A%20substantial%20victory%20for%20international%20students%20is%20the%20extension%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bcap-gap%26quot%3B%20provision.%20Under%20the%20previous%20system%2C%20F-1%20Optional%20Practical%20Training%20(OPT)%20could%20only%20be%20extended%20until%20October%201st.%20However%2C%20with%20the%20proposed%20rule%2C%20students%20can%20extend%20it%20until%20April%201st%20of%20the%20following%20year%20or%20until%20they%20receive%20their%20H-1B%20visa%2C%20whichever%20comes%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIncreased%20Site%20Visits%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20To%20combat%20fraud%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20IT%20consulting%20sector%2C%20USCIS%20will%20conduct%20more%20and%20stricter%20site%20visits.%20Inspectors%20may%20visit%20unannounced%2C%20interview%20officials%2C%20review%20records%2C%20and%20speak%20with%20employees.%20These%20measures%20aim%20to%20ensure%20that%20employers%20comply%20with%20the%20H-1B%20program%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStricter%20Definition%20Of%20%26quot%3BSpecialty%20Occupation%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20Another%20notable%20change%20is%20the%20stricter%20definition%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bspecialty%20occupation.%26quot%3B%20Under%20the%20new%20rule%2C%20there%20must%20be%20a%20direct%20relationship%20between%20the%20required%20degree%20field%20and%20the%20position's%20duties.%20This%20change%20could%20potentially%20lead%20to%20more%20Requests%20for%20Evidence%20(RFEs)%20and%20denials%20for%20deserving%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPublic%20Comment%20Period%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20The%20proposed%20changes%20to%20the%20H-1B%20program%20have%20not%20been%20set%20in%20stone.%20The%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20has%20initiated%20a%20%26quot%3Bpublic%20comment%20period%26quot%3B%20that%20runs%20until%20December%2022nd%2C%202023%2C%20allowing%20individuals%20to%20provide%20feedback%20and%20input.%20This%20presents%20an%20opportunity%20for%20immigrants%2C%20employers%2C%20and%20other%20stakeholders%20to%20shape%20the%20final%20regulations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20represents%20a%20significant%20step%20in%20modernizing%20and%20adapting%20the%20system%20to%20the%20needs%20of%20today's%20workforce.%20While%20some%20changes%20may%20face%20criticism%2C%20they%20also%20address%20long-standing%20issues%20and%20provide%20opportunities%20for%20entrepreneurs%2C%20students%2C%20and%20skilled%20professionals.%20It's%20important%20to%20note%20that%20these%20proposed%20changes%20are%20not%20final.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20rule%20is%20currently%20open%20for%20public%20comment%20until%20December%2022%2C%202023.%20After%20this%20period%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20will%20review%20the%20feedback%20and%20aim%20to%20publish%20a%20final%20rule%2C%20expected%20in%202024.%20This%20is%20a%20pivotal%20moment%20for%20anyone%20interested%20in%20the%20H-1B%20program%20to%20make%20their%20voices%20heard%20and%20contribute%20to%20the%20reform%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698089340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2018-04%2Fus-visa-us-immigration-istock_650x400_41524626692.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F5-big-changes-as-us-releases-proposed-tweaks-to-h-1b-process-4508357%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20H-1B%20visa%20program%20has%20long%20been%20a%20pivotal%20aspect%20of%20immigration%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20particularly%20for%20skilled%20professionals%20and%20international%20students.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F5-big-changes-as-us-releas