0in%20the%20book%20%E2%80%93%20Bishan%20Singh%20Bedi%3A%20Of%20Large%20Hearts%20and%20Large%20Stories%20%E2%80%93%20presents%20the%20warmed-hearted%20personality%20of%20Bedi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20months%20after%20%3Cem%3EMid-wicket%20Tales%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehad%20been%20published%2C%C2%A0Gideon%20Haigh%2C%20the%20cricket%20historian%20from%C2%A0%C2%A0%20Australia%2C%20wrote%20a%20generous%20review.%20He%20also%20sent%20it%20to%20his%20good%20friend%20in%20Delhi%2C%20the%20legendary%20cricketer%2C%20Bishan%20Singh%20Bedi.%20Gideon%20asked%20me%20to%20send%20Bedi%20a%20copy%2C%20which%20I%20(Giridhar)%20did%20with%20alacrity.%20Two%20days%20later%2C%20my%20phone%20rang.%20It%20was%20Bedi%2C%20exuberant%20and%20in%20his%20characteristic%20drawl%2C%20telling%20me%20he%20loved%20the%20book.%20I%20asked%20him%2C%20have%20you%20read%20it%20already%3F%20To%20which%20he%20replied%20he%20had%20only%20read%20a%20few%20chapters%20but%20liked%20what%20he%20had%20read%20so%20much%20that%20he%20had%20to%20immediately%20compliment%20us.%20I%20introduced%20him%20to%20Raghunath%20over%20email.%20Raghu%20was%20visiting%20his%20daughter%20in%20Delhi%20at%20that%20time%20and%20even%20before%20one%20could%20whip%20the%20bails%20off%20to%20a%20Bedi%20delivery%2C%20Raghu%20was%20having%20dinner%20at%20Bedi%E2%80%99s%20farmhouse!%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20Raghu%20met%20Bedi%20that%20first%20time%2C%20we%20had%20just%20begun%20work%20on%20our%20second%20book%2C%20%3Cem%3EFrom%20Mumbai%20to%20Durban%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20would%20narrate%20the%20history%20of%20Indian%20Test%20cricket%20through%20the%20stories%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20Test%20matches.%20As%20part%20of%20our%20research%20at%20that%20time%2C%20we%20were%20reaching%20out%20to%20cricketers%20and%20journalists%20to%20get%20their%20first-hand%20views%2C%20anecdotes%20and%20interesting%20snippets%20that%20would%20embellish%20the%20narration.%20That%20evening%20with%20Bedi%20was%20the%20first%20of%20our%20meetings%20with%20him.%20We%20did%20not%20have%20to%20persuade%20him%20because%20he%20had%20already%20made%20up%20his%20mind%20to%20help%20us.%20If%20you%C2%A0have%20browsed%20through%20the%20book%2C%20you%20will%20realise%20how%20much%20the%20great%20left-arm%20spinner%20contributed%20to%20it.%20He%20simply%20gave.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20he%20even%20remembers%20how%20much%20he%20told%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202015%2C%20Chennai%20was%20devastated%20by%20floods%2C%20rendering%20many%20people%20homeless.%20Lives%20were%20lost%2C%20houses%20ravaged.%20Bedi%2C%20living%20in%20Delhi%2C%20was%20getting%20desperately%20worried%20about%20his%20friends%20in%20Chennai.%20Not%20getting%20through%20to%20these%20people%20in%20Chennai%2C%20he%20called%20me%20to%20ask%20if%20his%20cricketer%20friends%20%E2%80%93%20W.%20V.%20Raman%2C%20Srikkanth%2C%20and%20a%20few%20others%20%E2%80%93%20and%20his%20new%20friend%2C%20Raghu%2C%20were%20safe.%20I%20had%20to%20admit%20that%20I%20did%20not%20know%20about%20the%20cricketers%20but%20assured%20him%20that%20Raghu%20was%20safe.%20Bedi%20was%20distraught%20and%20rang%20off%20to%20check%20with%20some%20other%20friends.%20That%E2%80%99s%20how%20Bedi%20is%20wired%2C%20genuinely%20concerned%20about%20his%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnder%20happier%20circumstances%20some%20months%20later%2C%20I%20got%20a%20call%20one%20evening%20at%209%20p.m.%20%E2%80%98Bishan%20here.%20I%20am%20in%20your%20town%2C%20at%20the%20Leela.%20Want%20to%20come%20over%20for%20dinner%3F%E2%80%99%20Since%20I%20live%20very%20close%20to%20The%20Leela%2C%20I%20was%20ringing%20his%20doorbell%20within%20minutes.%20Bedi%20welcomed%20me%20with%20a%20hug.%20And%20then%20mischievously%20he%20pointed%20me%20towards%20the%20shadowy%20corner%20of%20the%20room.%20Leaning%20against%20the%20wall%20was%20Sunil%20Joshi%2C%20former%20India%20left-arm%20spinner%20and%20in%20some%20ways%2C%20Bedi%E2%80%99s%20prot%C3%A9g%C3%A9.%20I%20told%20Bedi%20that%20like%20a%20good%20South%20Indian%2C%20I%20had%20finished%20dinner%20much%20before%20his%20call%20came.%20So%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98Ok%20have%20a%20beer.%E2%80%99%20Then%20rubbing%20his%20hands%20and%20leaning%20in%20his%20luxurious%20chair%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98When%20Sunil%20dropped%20in%20to%20see%20me%2C%20I%20thought%20I%20will%20call%20you%20over%20so%20that%20you%20can%20press%20him%20for%20some%20stories%20too.%E2%80%99%20Sunil%20of%20course%20is%20a%20lovely%20raconteur%20with%20an%20impish%20sense%20of%20humor.%20We%20set%20up%20a%20meeting%20for%20a%20later%20day%20where%20he%20shared%20some%20lovely%20stories%2C%20which%20you%20will%20also%20find%20in%20the%20book.%20That%20evening%20at%20The%20Leela%2C%20Bedi%20was%20in%20form.%20He%20told%20of%20his%20love%20for%20players%20like%20Pataudi%20and%20Jaisimha%3B%20of%20the%20spirit%20in%20which%20sport%20must%20be%20played.%20He%20narrated%20stories%20from%20the%20Indian%20tours%20to%20the%20West%20Indies%20and%20Pakistan%3B%20told%20us%20about%20a%20crazy%20helicopter%20ride%20in%20Guyana%3B%20and%20about%20a%20nervous%20Jaisimha%20always%20smoking%20like%20a%20chimney%20before%20his%20turn%20to%20bat.%20Then%2C%20with%20loud%20guffaws%2C%20he%20told%20us%20wicked%20stories%20about%20Lala%20Amarnath%20and%20his%20endless%C2%A0bragging.%20In%20the%20middle%20of%20all%20that%20he%20also%20chided%20me%20(and%20Raghunath%20in%20his%20absence)%20of%20not%20being%20forthright%20and%20critical%20enough%20about%20dubious%20bowling%20actions%20in%20our%20earlier%20book.%20He%20said%20we%20were%20being%20unnecessarily%20politically%20correct%20while%20talking%20of%20Muralitharan%20in%20our%20chapter%20on%20great%20off-spinners.%20Time%20flew%20as%20I%20soaked%20in%20the%20stories%2C%20and%20it%20was%20well%20past%20midnight%20when%20I%20reached%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20manuscript%20of%20our%20book%20%3Cem%3EFrom%20Mumbai%20to%20Durban%20%3C%2Fem%3Ereached%20its%20final%20stages%2C%20I%20emailed%20Bedi%20to%20reconfirm%20some%20of%20the%20stories%20and%20facts%20that%20he%20had%20told%20us.%20Raghu%20and%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20sure%20we%20would%20not%20be%20misquoting%20him.%20One%20of%20those%20really%20tall%20tales%20was%20about%20Lala%20Amarnath%E2%80%99s%20boast%20of%20doing%2010%2C000%20skips%20with%20the%20skipping%20rope%20in%2030%20minutes.%20We%20feared%20we%20might%20not%20have%20got%20the%20number%20right.%20Bishan%20is%20not%20so%20prompt%20on%20email%20and%20it%20was%20easier%20to%20speak%20to%20him%20over%20phone.%20As%20we%20repeated%20our%20query%2C%20he%20interjected%20to%20say%2C%20%E2%80%98Nah%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%2030%2C000%20that%20Lala%20claimed%20not%2010%2C000%20skips.%E2%80%99%20So%20what%20we%20thought%20was%20an%20already%20tall%20tale%20only%20became%20taller%20when%20we%20went%20back%20to%20Bedi%20to%20reconfirm.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20the%20fun%20of%20being%20acquainted%20with%20Bedi.%20We%20are%20pretty%20sure%20he%20is%20the%20same%20with%20almost%20everyone%2C%20friendly%20within%20minutes%20of%20shaking%20hands.%20That%20heart%2C%20it%20is%20large%2C%20it%20is%20generous%2C%20it%20overflows.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698085320000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F23233659%2FThe-Wire-52.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsport%2Fbishan-singh-bedi-was-full-of-life-and-genuinely-cared-for-his-people%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20excerpt%20from%20the%20book%20'Mid-Wicket%20Tales'%20presents%20the%20warmed-hearted%20personality%20of%20Bedi%2C%20his%20love%20for%20players%20Pataudi%20and%20Jaisimha%2C%20stories%20from%20his%20tours%20to%20the%20West%20Indies%20and%20Pakistan%2C%20and%20about%20his%20crazy%20helicopter%20ride%20in%20Guyana.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsport%2Fbishan-singh-bedi-was-full-of-life-and-genuinely-cared-for-his-people%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampU