3E%3Cstrong%3EBengaluru%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EChallenging%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20the%20Forest%20(Conservation)%20Amendment%20Act%202023%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20former%20civil%20servants%20and%20conservationists%20urged%20the%20court%20to%20declare%20the%20new%20Forest%20(Conservation)%20Amendment%20Act%202023%20%E2%80%9Cnull%20and%20void%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20They%20said%20it%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%20violation%20of%20several%20fundamental%20rights%20guaranteed%20under%20the%20constitution%2C%20as%20well%20as%20under%20the%20%E2%80%9Cestablished%20principles%20of%20Indian%20environmental%20jurisprudence%E2%80%9D.%20The%20court%20asked%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20writ%20petition.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EA%20controversial%20Bill%20that%20became%20Law%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnion%20environment%20minister%20Bhupender%20Yadav%20introduced%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2F164.100.47.4%2FBillsTexts%2FLSBillTexts%2FAsintroduced%2F80_2023_LS_ENG329202330923PM.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EForest%20(Conservation)%20Amendment%20Bill%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20March%2027%20this%20year%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Bill%20aimed%20to%20amend%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fbills_acts%2Fbills_parliament%2F2005%2Fbill53_2007010153_Handbook_of_Forest_Conservation_Act_1980_and_Forest_Conservation_Rules_2003.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EForest%20Conservation%20Act%20of%201980%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20provides%20for%20the%20conservation%20of%20forests%20across%20the%20country%20in%20several%20ways%20including%20restricting%20the%20use%20of%20forests%20for%20non-forest%20purposes%20(such%20as%20tourism).%20The%20Bill%20proposed%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fforest-governance-india-people%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eseveral%20drastic%20changes%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20the%20Act%20citing%2C%20among%20others%2C%20the%20importance%20of%20afforestation%20in%20meeting%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20carbon%20targets.%20Such%20a%20modification%20to%20the%20Act%2C%20experts%20had%20said%2C%20would%20mean%20that%20it%20would%20no%20longer%20apply%20to%20some%20forest%20lands%20(such%20as%20deemed%20forests%20and%20community%20forests)%20which%20are%20functional%20forests%20as%20per%20the%20dictionary%20meaning%20of%20the%20term%2C%20but%20not%20officially%20recorded%20as%20forests.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20the%20amendment%2C%20the%20new%20Act%20will%20apply%20only%20to%20lands%20notified%20as%20a%20forest%20under%20the%20Indian%20Forest%20Act%2C%201927%2C%20or%20those%20that%20have%20been%20officially%20recorded%20as%20a%20forest%20on%20or%20after%20October%2025%2C%201980.%20Yet%2C%20the%20Bill%20claimed%20that%20it%20clarified%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20scope%20of%20applicability%20of%20the%20Act%20upon%20various%20lands%20so%20as%20to%20remove%20ambiguities%20and%20bring%20clarity%E2%80%9D.%20Other%20issues%20that%20experts%20have%20pointed%20out%20included%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Bill%20would%20now%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20divert%20forest%20land%20within%20100%20kilometers%20of%20projects%20for%20%E2%80%9Cnational%20security%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cdefence%E2%80%9D%20purposes%20(this%20for%20instance%2C%20means%20that%20such%20projects%20in%20most%20of%20northeast%20India%20would%20not%20require%20forest%20clearance%20from%20the%20Forest%20Advisory%20Committee%20as%20was%20previously%20mandatory%20in%20the%20old%20Act)%2C%20and%20permits%20projects%20such%20as%20zoos%2C%20safaris%20and%20other%20ecotourism%20centers%20within%20forest%20land.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fcitizens-climate-action-groups-protest-against-the-passage-of-forest-conservation-amendment-bill%5C%22%3ECitizens%2C%20Climate%20Action%20Groups%20Protest%20Against%20the%20Passage%20of%20Forest%20Conservation%20Amendment%20Bill%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20several%20conservationists%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2F400-ecologists-write-to-environment-minister-against-amendments-to-forest-conservation-act%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Escientists%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmore-than-100-ex-civil-servants-question-new-forest-conservation-amendment-bill%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eformer%20civil%20servants%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3Cspan%3E%20and%20activists%20had%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fobjections-to-proposed-changes-to-forest-conservation-act-pour-in-from-all-corners%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eresponded%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20detail%20to%20these%20loopholes%20in%20the%20Amendment%2C%20they%20have%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fchanges-to-forest-conservation-act-heres-what-an-internal-document-of-the-govt-reveals%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ealleged%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20neither%20the%20Joint%20Parliamentary%20Committee%20that%20was%20set%20up%20to%20report%20on%20the%20Amendment%2C%20nor%20the%20Union%20Government%2C%20addressed%20any%20of%20these%20major%20concerns%20in%20the%20Committee%E2%80%99s%20Report%20on%20the%20same%2C%20and%20during%20the%20discussion%20that%20followed%20on%20the%20Bill%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20on%20August%202.%20The%20Committee%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20received%20about%201200%20memos%2C%20objections%20and%20addendum%20on%20the%20Bill%2C%20Pradyut%20Bordoloi%2C%20a%20Congress%20MP%20from%20Assam%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fobjections-to-proposed-changes-to-forest-conservation-act-pour-in-from-all-corners%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etold%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%20Science%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20June%20this%20year.%20The%20Lok%20Sabha%20cleared%20the%20Bill%20on%20July%2026%2C%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20on%20August%202%2C%20and%20the%20Bill%20also%20received%20Presidential%20Assent%20shortly%20thereafter%20(August%204).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F19195854%2Fimage-1141.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F19195854%2Fimage-1141.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F19195854%2Fimage-1141-300x129.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F19195854%2Fimage-1141-1024x440.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-664010%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22516%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EProtest%20against%20the%20Forest%20Conservation%20Amendment%20Bill%20in%20Hasdeo%2C%20Chhattisgarh.%20Photo%3A%20By%20special%20arrangement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPetition%20in%20SC%20challenges%20new%20Act%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESeveral%20former%20civil%20servants%20and%20conservationists%20filed%20a%20writ%20petition%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%E2%80%93%20which%20the%20Court%20heard%20on%20October%2020%20%E2%80%93%20saying%20that%20the%20new%20Act%20is%20%E2%80%9Cunconstitutional%E2%80%9D%20and%20should%20be%20held%20%E2%80%9Cnull%20and%20void%E2%80%9D%20since%20it%20violates%20several%20fundamental%20rights%20guaranteed%20under%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%2C%20as%20well%20as%20under%20the%20%E2%80%9Cestablished%20principles%20of%20Indian%20environmental%20jurisprudence%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CRampant%20diversion%20of%20forest%20land%20for%20all%20varieties%20of%20purposes%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20which%2C%20as%20per%20experts%2C%20the%20new%20Act%20facilitates%20%E2%80%93%20will%20cause%20%E2%80%9Cunrestricted%20deforestation%E2%80%9D%20and%20this%20amounts%20to%20a%20violation%20of%20the%20fundamental%20right%20guaranteed%20to%20Indians%20under%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20to%20live%20in%20a%20pollution-free%20environment%2C%20the%20petition%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20other%20rights%20that%20the%20petition%20says%20will%20be%20violated%20with%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20new%20Act%20are%20Articles%2014%2C%20along%20with%20Articles%2048A%2C%2051%20C%2C%20and%2051%20A(G)%20of%20the%20constitution.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmong%20the%20%E2%80%9Cestablished%20principles%20of%20Indian%20environmental%20jurisprudence%E2%80%9D%20that%20will%20be%20violated%20are%20the%20precautionary%20principle%20(which%2C%20as%20per%20the%20ruling%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20a%201996%20order%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmakes%20it%20mandatory%20for%20the%20State%20Government%20to%20anticipate%2C%20prevent%20and%20attack%20the%20causes%20of%20environmental%20degradation%E2%80%9D)%20and%20the%20public%20trust%20doctrine%20(which%20mandates%20that%20public%20lands%C2%A0%20%E2%80%93%20in%20this%20case%2C%20forests%20held%20by%20the%20government%20of%20India%20%E2%80%93%20are%20held%20by%20the%20government%20on%20behalf%20of%20all%20people%20and%20future%20generations%2C%20and%20that%20the%20government%20therefore%20is%20liable%20to%20protect%20forests).%20Another%20is%20the%20principle%20of%20non-regression%2C%20which%20holds%20that%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20humanity%2C%20no%20environmental%20law%20can%20be%20diluted%20or%20regressed%20but%20only%20improved.%20The%20petition%2C%20like%20the%20comments%20provided%20on%20the%20Amendment%20Bill%20by%20institutes%2C%20research%20organizations%20and%20independent%20scholars%2C%20holds%20that%20the%20new%20Act%20is%20a%20regression%20to%20the%20old%20one%20in%20that%20it%20will%20open%20up%20large%20tracts%20of%20forest%20land%20to%20deforestation%20and%20change.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20petition%20%E2%80%93%20which%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20accessed%20%E2%80%93%20argues%20that%20the%20new%20Act%20%E2%80%9Cintroduces%20a%20regulatory%20regime%20that%20facilitates%20a%20regression%20in%20the%20nature%20and%20extent%20of%20protection%20that%20forests%20were%20afforded%20earlier%E2%80%9D.%20It%20details%20how%20the%20Act%20goes%20against%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20order%20in%201996%20(T.%20Godavarman%20Vs%20Union%20of%20India)%2C%20which%20permitted%20that%20forest%20lands%20that%20are%20not%20officially%20recorded%20as%20forests%20but%20which%20are%20functional%20forests%20as%20per%20the%20dictionary%20meaning%20of%20the%20term%2C%20to%20be%20recognized%20and%20protected%20as%20such.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%201996%20order%20had%20held%20that%20states%20form%20State%20Expert%20Committees%2C%20and%20develop%20reports%20that%20quantify%20and%20identify%20forest%20lands%20in%20each%20state.%20However%2C%20none%20of%20these%20are%20in%20the%20public%20domain%2C%20and%20it%20is%20not%20clear%20if%20all%20states%20have%20these%20Committees%20or%20the%20Committees%20have%20submitted%20their%20reports%20either%2C%20clarified%20Prakriti%20Srivastava%2C%20one%20of%20the%20petitioners.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20examining%20Kerala%E2%80%99s%20State%20Expert%20Committee%20report%2C%20it%20is%20evident%20that%20it%20was%20put%20together%20in%20haste%20with%20no%20reference%20to%20the%20locations%20of%20the%20forests%20in%20the%20state%2C%20and%20without%20any%20ground%20truthing%2C%20physical%20cadastral%20surveys%20or%20demarcation%20of%20these%20lands%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20petition%20reads.%20%E2%80%9CSEC%20reports%20submitted%20by%20other%20states%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20of%20similar%20poor%20quality.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESrivastava%2C%20a%20former%20Kerala%20cadre%20IFS%20officer%20who%20retired%20as%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20Principal%20Chief%20Conservator%20of%20Forests%20noted%20that%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Kerala%2C%20if%20a%20proper%20SEC%20report%20had%20been%20filed%2C%20it%20would%20have%20notified%20parts%20of%20Chinnakanal%20and%20Pullivasal%20in%20Idukki%20district%20as%20forest%20lands%20too.%20However%2C%20these%20areas%20were%20not%20notified%20or%20mentioned%20in%20the%20SEC%20and%20as%20a%20result%2C%20the%20areas%20are%20now%20overridden%20by%20resorts.%20Incidentally%2C%20the%20loss%20of%20wildlife%20habitat%20and%20conversion%20of%20wild%20lands%20here%20have%20caused%20habitat%20fragmentation%20%E2%80%93%20a%20possible%20reason%20why%20Arikomban%2C%20the%20famed%20rice-eating%20elephant%20of%20Idukki%20district%20took%20to%20stealing%20rice%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%20and%20would%20venture%20into%20human-dominated%20areas%20(where%20once%20forest%20land%20stood)%20to%20look%20for%20easy%20food%2C%20per%20locals%20and%20elephant%20behavior%20specialists%2C%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%20Science%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20had%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fchanging-landscapes-altered-realities-the-making-of-arikomban%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESrivastava%E2%80%99s%20report%20in%20the%20late%201990s%20submitted%20to%20the%20state%20forest%20department%20when%20she%20was%20posted%20in%20the%20area%20highlighted%20that%20the%20land%20should%20not%20be%20diverted%20for%20a%20settlement%20for%20landless%20tribal%20communities%3B%20this%20report%2C%20media%20articles%20have%20pointed%20out%2C%20however%2C%20was%20ignored%20and%20forest%20land%20distributed%20to%20people.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Forest%20Survey%20of%20India%20%E2%80%93%20which%20compiles%20biannual%20India%E2%80%99s%20State%20of%20Forest%20Reports%20%E2%80%93%20should%20have%20compiled%20data%20from%20the%20SECs%20and%20included%20these%20in%20their%20reports%2C%20but%20this%20has%20not%20been%20done%20either%2C%20Srivastava%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20ministry%20also%20claimed%20that%20the%20old%20Act%20is%20being%20modified%20to%20ensure%20that%20people%20will%20now%20be%20encouraged%20to%20plant%20trees%20on%20their%20lands%20which%20will%20help%20increase%20the%20carbon%20stock%20of%20the%20country%20through%20afforestation%20and%20plantations.%20However%2C%20where%20is%20the%20proof%2C%20the%20data%2C%20that%20people%20are%20currently%20not%20planting%20trees%20fearing%20the%20old%20Act%2C%20asked%20Srivastava.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20submissions%20by%20the%20Ministry%20are%20only%20anecdotal%20and%20not%20data-based%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPer%20the%20petition%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cprincipal%20Act%20is%20effective%20and%20practical%20and%20the%20need%20of%20the%20hour%20is%20better%20implementation%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20petition%20noted.%20%E2%80%9CState-level%20initiatives%20under%20the%20umbrella%20of%20the%20principal%20Act%20could%20have%20been%20considered%20to%20encourage%20tree%20plantation%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20read.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20ministry%20submitted%20%E2%80%9Cfalse%20and%20incomplete%20information%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20petition%20also%20alleges%20that%20the%20Union%20Environment%20Ministry%20provided%20%E2%80%9Cfalse%20and%20incomplete%E2%80%9D%20information%20to%20the%20JPC%20and%20the%20JPC%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20%E2%80%9Cbelieved%20the%20Ministry%E2%80%99s%20submissions%20without%20any%20scientific%20examination%20or%20scrutiny%20of%20the%20documents%E2%80%9D.%20The%20petition%20also%20points%20out%20that%20though%20numerous%20experts%20including%20conservationists%20and%20legal%20policy%20researchers%20including%20several%20of%20the%20petitioners%20in%20this%20writ%20petition%20raised%20concerns%20regarding%20all%20these%20issues%20in%20the%20Amendment%2C%20these%20were%20not%20addressed%20by%20the%20JPC%20or%20corrective%20measures%20taken%20in%20the%20draft%20Bill.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20the%20petition%2C%20it%20is%3A%20%E2%80%9Capparent%20that%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%202023%20Amendment%20Act%20will%20cumulatively%20cause%20extensive%20and%20unbridled%20damage%20to%20the%20forests%20of%20India.%20These%20amendments%20fundamentally%20change%20the%20entire%20object%20and%20purpose%20of%20the%20FC%20Act%20as%20well%20as%20the%20regulatory%20framework%20built%20under%20it.The%20amended%20Forest%20(Conservation)%20Act%20is%20now%20a%20new%20legislation%2C%20bearing%20little%20resemblance%20with%20the%20principal%20Act.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20petitioners%20include%20two%20former%20secretaries%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Environment%2C%20Forest%20and%20Climate%20Change%20(MoEFCC)%20M.K.%20Ranjitsinh%20and%20Meena%20Gupta%2C%20and%20conservationist%20and%20former%20member%20of%20the%20National%20Board%20for%20Wild%20Life%20Prerna%20Singh%20Bindra.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EWe%20take%20this%20battle%20to%20the%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20set%20aside%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FForest%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23Forest%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FConservation%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23Conservation%3C%2Fa%3E%20Amendment%20Act%202023%20which%20is%20tailored%20to%20remove%20vast%20swathes%20of%20forest%20land%20from%20legal%20protection%3B%20throwing%20them%20open%20for%20diversion%20for%20pvt%2C%20commercial%20interests%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20prerna%20singh%20bindra%20%F0%9F%90%98%F0%9F%90%85%F0%9F%90%BE%20(%40prernabindra)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fprernabindra%2Fstatus%2F1715557777974718813%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EOctober%2021%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20a%20fight%20to%20conserve%20%23India%E2%80%99s%20wealth%20of%20%23forests%20%26amp%3B%20precious%20%23wildlife%2C%20preserve%20our%20natural%20%26amp%3B%20cultural%20heritage%2C%20save%20the%20%23ecosystems%20crucial%20for%20our%20ecological%20%26amp%3B%20financial%20security%E2%80%A6It%20is%20a%20battle%20to%20preserve%20our%20%23forests%2C%20leave%20a%20living%2C%20viable%20%23environment%20for%20our%20children.%20It%20is%20a%20battle%20to%20save%20the%20idea%20of%20%23India.%20Lest%20we%20forget%20our%20forests%20and%20our%20%23wildlife%20are%20part%20of%20the%20fabric%20of%20the%20country%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fprernabindra%2Fstatus%2F1715557772186591737%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etweeted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Bindra%20on%20October%2021.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2023%2F40155%2F40155_2023_4_66_47796_Order_20-Oct-2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eheard%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20petition%20on%20October%2020%20and%20has%20given%20the%20Union%20government%20six%20weeks%20to%20respond.%20The%20petition%20is%20the%20last%20legal%20resort%20%E2%80%93%20an%20almost%20frantic%20last%20attempt%20%E2%80%93%20to%20prevent%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20Act%20in%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20we%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20done%20this%20then%20it%20would%20have%20been%20a%20lost%20cause%20anyways%E2%80%A6so%20we%20have%20hope%20because%20we%20believe%20this%20is%20something%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20fought%20out%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Srivastava.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20order%20itself%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Godavarman%20case%20in%201996%2C%20which%20detailed%20how%20forests%20should%20be%20identified%20%E2%80%93%20that%20the%20new%20Act%20is%20going%20against.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20if%20the%20court%20does%20not%20address%20the%20concerns%20in%20the%20petition%2C%20what%20then%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThen%20I%20guess%20we%20must%20just%20accept%20the%20fact%20that%20we%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20perish%20very%20soon%2C%E2%80%9D%20Srivastava%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20talking%20about%20addressing%20human%20wildlife%20conflict%20and%20climate%20change%20on%20one%20hand%2C%20and%20on%20the%20other%2C%20cutting%20the%20very%20branch%20we%20are%20sitting%20on%20%5Bby%20implementing%20the%20new%20Act%5D.%20It%20is%20all%20just%20doublespeak%20and%20our%20actions%20don%E2%80%99t%20align%20with%20our%20words.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698076103000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2F04170315%2F15693039226_bc366e1bf3_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fconstitutionality-of-forest-conservation-act-2023-challenged-in-sc-centre-to-respond-in-6-weeks%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20petition%20said%20Forest%20(Conservation)%20Amendment%20Act%202023%20is%20in%20violation%20of%20several%20fundamental%20rights%20guaranteed%20under%20the%20constitution%2C%20as%20well%20as%20under%20the%20'established%20principles%20of%20Indian%20environmental